      "description": "Available now is a mechanically sorted 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S), a pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering. This unit features the 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, known for its high power-to-displacement ratio and unique exhaust note. The drivetrain is paired with a crisp 5-speed manual transmission and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. The chassis retains its legendary 50/50 weight distribution and sophisticated four-wheel double-wishbone suspension, providing exceptional lateral grip and communicative steering. Recent service includes a full cooling system refresh and a verified compression test confirming strong, even pulses across all rotor faces. While the aesthetic reflects its age with minor cosmetic wear, the mechanical integrity remains high, making it an ideal candidate for a purist driver or a dedicated project.",
